caption.p: Influenza B virus inoculation caused pathology in the nasal turbinates, trachea and lungs of trees shrews. Nasal turbinates ( a, d, g, j, m, p), trachea ( b, e, h, k, n, q), and lungs ( c, f, i, l, o, r) were collected at 2, 4 and 6 days post inoculation (DPI) from animals inoculated with either Yamagata strain B/Guangzhou/12/2016 or Victoria strain B/Guangzhou/0215/2012 and stained with hematoxylin and eosin. Images were examined at magnification of × 200
